ull,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to awake"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to incite, to induce, to instigate","examples":[{"text":"فَيَنْبَغِي أَنْ نَسْأَلَهُ عَمَّا بَعَثَهُ عَلَى ذٰلِكَ، لَعَلَّ لَهُ عُذْرًا.","english":"In Baghdad"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to raise"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to resurrect","examples":[{"text":"فَأَمَاتَهُ اللَّهُ مِائَةَ عَامٍ ثُمَّ بَعَثَهُ","english":"So Allah caused him to die for a hundred years then brought him back to life."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to send","examples":[{"text":"وَإِنْ خِفْتُمْ شِقَاقَ بَيْنِهِمَا فَابْعَثُوا حَكَمًا مِنْ أَهْلِهِ وَحَكَمًا مِنْ أَهْلِهَا","english":"And if ye fear a breach between them twain, send an arbiter from his folk and an arbiter from her folk. If they desire amendment, Allah will make them of one mind. Lo! Allah is ever Knower, Aware."},{"text":"هُوَ ٱلَّذِي بَعَثَ فِي ٱلۡأُمِّيِّـۧنَ رَسُولٗا مِّنۡهُمۡ يَتۡلُواْ عَلَيۡهِمۡ ءَايَٰتِهِۦ وَيُزَكِّيهِمۡ وَيُعَلِّمُهُمُ ٱلۡكِتَٰبَ وَٱلۡحِكۡمَةَ وَإِن كَانُواْ مِن قَبۡلُ لَفِي ضَلَٰلٖ مُّبِينٖ.","english":"He it is Who hath sent among the unlettered ones a messenger of their own, to recite unto them His revelations and to make them grow, and to teach them the Scripture and wisdom, though heretofore they were indeed in error manifest."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَعَثَ (baʕaṯa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sending out, emission, dispatching, delegation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"resurrection","examples":[{"text":"إِنْ كُنْتُمْ فِي رَيْبٍ مِنَ ٱلْبَعْثِ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"awakening, renaissance, revival, arousal, evocation"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ba.ʕa.θa/","/baʕθ/"]}